The paper discusses the intersection between ethics and engineering in autonomous systems, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also addresses issues related to the conceptual design (cs.ET) and verification (cs.SE) of autonomous systems, as well as transparency and accountability (cs.CYBER) in their deployment. Additionally, the paper discusses intentional misuse of AI systems, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
